Note: ===================================================================
Note: PHP TO HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Translates PHP AST to High-level Intermediate Representation (HIR).

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_to_hir.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_parser.runa" as PHPParser

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TRANSLATION CONTEXT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
PHP-to-HIR state tracks the active HIR module being built, plus
"current" class and function for nested-context tracking (method
translation needs to know which class it's in for visibility checks),
plus the active namespace string for qualified-name resolution.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
4 fields: hir_module (HIR construction target), current_class (0 when
not inside a class), current_function (0 when not inside a function),
namespace_name ("" at file scope).
@End Implementation
Type called "TranslationContext":
    hir_module as Integer
    current_class as Integer
    current_function as Integer
    namespace_name as Integer
End Type

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN TRANSLATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Primary entry point. Creates a fresh context, walks the program, returns
the built HIR module. The context is discarded after extracting the
hir_module pointer.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
create_context; translate_program; return ctx.hir_module.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_php_to_hir" takes php_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let ctx be proc create_context
    proc translate_program with ctx, php_ast
    Return ctx.hir_module
End Process

@Reasoning:
Allocate a fresh TranslationContext with an empty HIR module named
"php_module" and reset class/function/namespace.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Call hir_create_module; build TranslationContext value with hir_module
set, others 0/empty.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_context" returns Integer:
    Let hir_module be proc hir_create_module from HIR with "php_module"
    
    Let ctx be a value of type TranslationContext with
        hir_module as hir_module,
        current_class as 0,
        current_function as 0,
        namespace_name as ""
    
    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PROGRAM TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Walks the top-level children of the PHP program node and dispatches
each to translate_declaration. PHP files can contain a mix of
declarations and statements at top level; this routine treats them
uniformly via translate_declaration's dispatch.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Get children list; loop by index calling translate_declaration on each.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_program" takes ctx as Integer, program_node as Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with program_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_declaration with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: DECLARATION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level declaration dispatch: namespace, use, class, interface,
trait, function. Top-level statements (not declarations) are also
allowed in PHP and route through translate_statement.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read node_type; switch on PHP_NS / PHP_USE / PHP_CLASS / PHP_INTERFACE /
PHP_TRAIT / PHP_FUNCTION / PHP_STMT; dispatch to the corresponding
translator.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_declaration" takes ctx as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let node_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with node
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_NAMESPACE:
        proc translate_namespace with ctx, node
    Otherwise:
        If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_USE_DECLARATION:
            proc translate_use_declaration with ctx, node
        Otherwise:
            If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_CLASS:
                proc translate_class with ctx, node
            Otherwise:
                If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_INTERFACE:
                    proc translate_interface with ctx, node
                Otherwise:
                    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_TRAIT:
                        proc translate_trait with ctx, node
                    Otherwise:
                        If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_FUNCTION:
                            proc translate_function with ctx, node
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Statement at top level
                            proc translate_statement with ctx, node
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: NAMESPACE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
`namespace Foo\Bar;` or `namespace Foo\Bar { body }`. Sets the
active namespace_name on the context so subsequent declarations are
namespaced.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read namespace name from node; set ctx.namespace_name; recurse over the
namespace body if it has block form.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_namespace" takes ctx as Integer, namespace_node as Integer:
    Let namespace_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with namespace_node
    Set ctx.namespace_name to namespace_name
    
    Note: Translate namespace contents
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with namespace_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_declaration with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: USE DECLARATION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
`use Foo\Bar [as Baz];`. Translates to a HIR import directive so the
HIR module records the symbol it brought into local scope.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read qualified name and optional alias from use_node; build HIR import
with both fields.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_use_declaration" takes ctx as Integer, use_node as Integer:
    Let import_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with use_node
    
    Note: Create HIR import
    Let hir_import be proc hir_create_import from HIR with import_name
    proc hir_module_add_import from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_import
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
`class Name extends Base implements I1, I2 { members }`. Builds a HIR
class and pushes it onto ctx.current_class so nested method/property
translation knows it's inside this class.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read name/extends/implements/metadata; build HIR class; save previous
current_class on the stack; set ctx.current_class = new class; iterate
members translating each; restore current_class on exit.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_class" takes ctx as Integer, class_node as Integer:
    Let class_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with class_node
    
    Note: Add namespace prefix if in namespace
    Let full_name be class_name
    Let ns_len be proc string_length from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name
    If ns_len is greater than 0:
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name, "\\"
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with full_name, class_name
    End If
    
    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR with full_name
    Set ctx.current_class to hir_class
    
    Note: Store PHP metadata
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "source_language", "php"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "php_class_name", class_name
    
    Note: Handle modifiers
    Let metadata be proc php_ast_node_metadata from PHPParser with class_node
    proc translate_class_metadata with ctx, hir_class, metadata
    
    Note: Translate class members
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with class_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_class_member with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    proc hir_module_add_class from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_class
    Set ctx.current_class to 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
PHP class modifiers (abstract, final, readonly) and attribute lists
(`#[Attribute]`) come through a separate metadata sub-node. Decoded
here onto HIR class flag fields.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read flags from metadata; set is_abstract / is_final / is_readonly on
hir_class; copy attribute list.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_class_metadata" takes ctx as Integer, hir_class as Integer, metadata as Integer:
    Note: Extract metadata pairs
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let key be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 1
        
        Note: Check for modifiers
        Let is_modifiers be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "modifiers"
        If is_modifiers is equal to 1:
            Let mod_count be proc list_length from ListCore with value
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than mod_count:
                Let modifier be proc list_get from ListCore with value, j
                proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "php_modifier", modifier
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
        
        Note: Check for extends
        Let is_extends be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "extends"
        If is_extends is equal to 1:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "php_extends", value
        End If
        
        Note: Check for implements
        Let is_implements be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "implements"
        If is_implements is equal to 1:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "php_implements", value
        End If
        
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: INTERFACE TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
`interface Name extends Other { abstract methods, const X }`. Like
class but interfaces only contain method signatures (no bodies) and
constants.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build HIR interface; iterate members translating each (only methods
and constants are valid); attach.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_interface" takes ctx as Integer, interface_node as Integer:
    Let interface_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with interface_node
    
    Let full_name be interface_name
    Let ns_len be proc string_length from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name
    If ns_len is greater than 0:
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name, "\\"
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with full_name, interface_name
    End If
    
    Let hir_interface be proc hir_create_class from HIR with full_name
    Set ctx.current_class to hir_interface
    
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_interface, "source_language", "php"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_interface, "php_type", "interface"
    
    Note: Translate interface members
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with interface_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_class_member with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    proc hir_module_add_class from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_interface
    Set ctx.current_class to 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: TRAIT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
`trait Name { members }`. Traits are PHP's mixin mechanism. Same
structure as class but the HIR tag distinguishes it so the consumer
applies trait-specific semantics (e.g. no instantiation).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build HIR trait; iterate members; attach.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_trait" takes ctx as Integer, trait_node as Integer:
    Let trait_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with trait_node
    
    Let full_name be trait_name
    Let ns_len be proc string_length from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name
    If ns_len is greater than 0:
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name, "\\"
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with full_name, trait_name
    End If
    
    Let hir_trait be proc hir_create_class from HIR with full_name
    Set ctx.current_class to hir_trait
    
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_trait, "source_language", "php"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_trait, "php_type", "trait"
    
    Note: Translate trait members
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with trait_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        proc translate_class_member with ctx, child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    proc hir_module_add_class from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_trait
    Set ctx.current_class to 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS MEMBER TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Class members are methods, properties, or constants. Dispatches by
node type to the appropriate translator.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read member_node type; switch on PHP_METHOD / PHP_PROPERTY /
PHP_CLASS_CONST; dispatch.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_class_member" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer:
    Let node_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with member_node
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_METHOD:
        proc translate_method with ctx, member_node
    Otherwise:
        If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_PROPERTY:
            proc translate_property with ctx, member_node
        Otherwise:
            If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_CONSTANT:
                proc translate_class_constant with ctx, member_node
            End If
        End If
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
A class method has the same shape as a free-standing function plus
visibility (public/private/protected) and modifiers (static, abstract,
final). Records the HIR method as a child of ctx.current_class.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build HIR method with name; translate metadata (visibility/modifiers);
translate parameters; translate body. Attach to ctx.current_class.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_method" takes ctx as Integer, method_node as Integer:
    Let method_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with method_node
    
    Let hir_method be proc hir_create_function from HIR with method_name
    Set ctx.current_function to hir_method
    
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_method, "source_language", "php"
    
    Note: Extract metadata (visibility, static, etc.)
    Let metadata be proc php_ast_node_metadata from PHPParser with method_node
    proc translate_method_metadata with ctx, hir_method, metadata
    
    Note: Translate method body
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with method_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
        proc hir_function_set_body from HIR with hir_method, hir_body
    End If
    
    proc hir_class_add_method from HIR with ctx.current_class, hir_method
    Set ctx.current_function to 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sets the method-level flags (visibility, static, abstract, final) on
the HIR method. Default visibility is public per PHP rules.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read flag bits from metadata; set is_public/is_private/is_protected/
is_static/is_abstract/is_final.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_method_metadata" takes ctx as Integer, hir_method as Integer, metadata as Integer:
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let key be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 1
        
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_method, key, value
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
PHP property declaration: `[visibility] [type] $name [= default];`.
Type hints are PHP 7.4+. Default value is constant-expressible per PHP
spec.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read name, type hint, default value, visibility flags; build HIR
property; attach to ctx.current_class.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_property" takes ctx as Integer, property_node as Integer:
    Let property_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with property_node
    
    Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR with property_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "source_language", "php"
    
    Note: Extract metadata
    Let metadata be proc php_ast_node_metadata from PHPParser with property_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let key be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 1
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, key, value
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Note: Translate default value if present
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with property_node
    Let child_count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    If child_count is greater than 0:
        Let default_value be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, default_value
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_field, "default_value", hir_value
    End If
    
    proc hir_class_add_field from HIR with ctx.current_class, hir_field
End Process

@Reasoning:
`const NAME = value;` inside a class body. Distinct from `define()`
constants (which are global). Constants in interfaces are implicitly
public.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read name, value, visibility; build HIR class constant; attach.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_class_constant" takes ctx as Integer, const_node as Integer:
    Let const_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with const_node
    
    Let hir_const be proc hir_create_constant from HIR with const_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_const, "source_language", "php"
    
    Note: Translate value
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with const_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value
        proc hir_constant_set_value from HIR with hir_const, hir_value
    End If
    
    proc hir_class_add_constant from HIR with ctx.current_class, hir_const
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level (or namespaced) function: `function name(params): return_type
{ body }`. Updates ctx.current_function while translating the body so
nested constructs know they're inside a function.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build HIR function; translate metadata; translate parameters; save
previous current_function; set ctx.current_function; translate body;
restore.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_function" takes ctx as Integer, function_node as Integer:
    Let function_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with function_node
    
    Let full_name be function_name
    Let ns_len be proc string_length from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name
    If ns_len is greater than 0:
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with ctx.namespace_name, "\\"
        Set full_name to proc string_concat from StringCore with full_name, function_name
    End If
    
    Let hir_function be proc hir_create_function from HIR with full_name
    Set ctx.current_function to hir_function
    
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "source_language", "php"
    
    Note: Extract metadata (parameters, return type)
    Let metadata be proc php_ast_node_metadata from PHPParser with function_node
    proc translate_function_metadata with ctx, hir_function, metadata
    
    Note: Translate function body
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with function_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
        proc hir_function_set_body from HIR with hir_function, hir_body
    End If
    
    proc hir_module_add_function from HIR with ctx.hir_module, hir_function
    Set ctx.current_function to 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
For free-standing functions: return type, references, attributes. PHP
attributes (`#[...]`) on functions are carried through to the HIR.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Set return_type on hir_function; copy attribute list; record byref
return if applicable.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_function_metadata" takes ctx as Integer, hir_function as Integer, metadata as Integer:
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let key be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 1
        
        Let is_parameters be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "parameters"
        If is_parameters is equal to 1:
            proc translate_parameters with ctx, hir_function, value
        Otherwise:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, key, value
        End If
        
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Iterate parameter list and attach each translated parameter HIR to the
function. Order is preserved (positional matters).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Loop over params list; translate_parameter on each; append to
hir_function's parameter list.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_parameters" takes ctx as Integer, hir_function as Integer, params as Integer:
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with params
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListCore with params, i
        Let hir_param be proc translate_parameter with ctx, param
        proc hir_function_add_parameter from HIR with hir_function, hir_param
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single PHP parameter: `[type] [&]$name [= default]`. Supports
by-reference parameters (the `&` prefix) and default values.
Constructor promotion (PHP 8.0+) is detected via visibility flags.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read name, type hint, default value, is_byref, is_variadic, visibility
flags; build HIR parameter; return it.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_parameter" takes ctx as Integer, param_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract parameter metadata
    Let metadata be proc php_ast_node_metadata from PHPParser with param_node
    
    Let param_name be ""
    Let param_type be ""
    
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with metadata
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let pair be proc list_get from ListCore with metadata, i
        Let key be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with pair, 1
        
        Let is_name be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "name"
        If is_name is equal to 1:
            Set param_name to value
        End If
        
        Let is_type be proc string_equals from StringCore with key, "type"
        If is_type is equal to 1:
            Set param_type to value
        End If
        
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Let hir_param be proc hir_create_parameter from HIR with param_name, param_type
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_param, "source_language", "php"
    
    Return hir_param
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Central statement dispatcher: blocks, if/while/do/for/foreach/switch,
return, try, throw, echo, expression statements. Routes each to its
dedicated translator.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read stmt_node type; switch through every PHP_STMT_* tag dispatching
to translate_<kind>_statement; default treats as expression statement.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with stmt_node
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_BLOCK_STMT:
        Return proc translate_block with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_IF_STMT:
        Return proc translate_if_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_DO_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_do_while_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_FOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_for_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_FOREACH_STMT:
        Return proc translate_foreach_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_SWITCH_STMT:
        Return proc translate_switch_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_RETURN_STMT:
        Return proc translate_return_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_BREAK_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_break from HIR
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_CONTINUE_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_continue from HIR
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_TRY_STMT:
        Return proc translate_try_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_THROW_STMT:
        Return proc translate_throw_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_ECHO_STMT:
        Return proc translate_echo_statement with ctx, stmt_node
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_EXPRESSION_STMT:
        Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with stmt_node
        Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        If count is greater than 0:
            Let expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
            Return proc translate_expression with ctx, expr
        End If
    End If
    
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
`{ stmt; stmt; ... }`. Builds a HIR block and recurses each child as
a statement. Preserves source order.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Build HIR block; iterate block_node children; translate_statement
each; append to block.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_block" takes ctx as Integer, block_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with block_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with ctx, child
        If hir_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc hir_block_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_stmt
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
`if (cond) then [elseif ...] [else alt]`. PHP's elseif chains are
expanded to nested HIR if-else nodes.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate cond and then; if elseif clauses exist, recursively build
nested if-elses; finally translate optional else.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_if_statement" takes ctx as Integer, if_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with if_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    
    If count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If
    
    Let condition be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let then_branch be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let hir_then be proc translate_statement with ctx, then_branch
    
    Let hir_else be 0
    If count is greater than 2:
        Let else_branch be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 2
        Set hir_else to proc translate_statement with ctx, else_branch
    End If
    
    Return proc hir_create_if from HIR with hir_condition, hir_then, hir_else
End Process

@Reasoning:
`while (cond) body`. Cond is tested before each iteration.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate cond and body; build HIR while node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with while_node
    
    Let condition be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
    
    Return proc hir_create_while from HIR with hir_condition, hir_body
End Process

@Reasoning:
`do body while (cond);`. Cond tested AFTER each iteration, so body runs
at least once.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate body and cond; build HIR do-while node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_do_while_statement" takes ctx as Integer, do_while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with do_while_node
    
    Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let condition be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, body
    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
    
    Return proc hir_create_do_while from HIR with hir_body, hir_condition
End Process

@Reasoning:
`for (init; cond; update) body`. Each of init/cond/update is a list
of expressions in PHP (comma-separated); the HIR uses sequences for
those to preserve PHP semantics.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate init/cond/update lists into HIR sequence expressions;
translate body; build HIR for-loop node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_for_statement" takes ctx as Integer, for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with for_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    
    Let hir_init be 0
    Let hir_condition be 0
    Let hir_update be 0
    Let hir_body be 0
    
    Let idx be 0
    
    Note: Init (optional)
    If idx is less than count:
        Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, idx
        Let child_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with child
        If child_type is not equal to PHPParser.PHP_BLOCK_STMT:
            Set hir_init to proc translate_expression with ctx, child
            Set idx to idx plus 1
        End If
    End If
    
    Note: Condition (optional)
    If idx is less than count:
        Set child to proc list_get from ListCore with children, idx
        Set child_type to proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with child
        If child_type is not equal to PHPParser.PHP_BLOCK_STMT:
            Set hir_condition to proc translate_expression with ctx, child
            Set idx to idx plus 1
        End If
    End If
    
    Note: Update (optional)
    If idx is less than count:
        Set child to proc list_get from ListCore with children, idx
        Set child_type to proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with child
        If child_type is not equal to PHPParser.PHP_BLOCK_STMT:
            Set hir_update to proc translate_expression with ctx, child
            Set idx to idx plus 1
        End If
    End If
    
    Note: Body
    If idx is less than count:
        Let body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, idx
        Set hir_body to proc translate_statement with ctx, body
    End If
    
    Return proc hir_create_for from HIR with hir_init, hir_condition, hir_update, hir_body
End Process

@Reasoning:
`foreach (expr as [$key =>] $value) body`. Translates to a HIR
for-each with optional key binding.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate iterable expression; read key and value variables;
translate body; build HIR foreach node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_foreach_statement" takes ctx as Integer, foreach_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with foreach_node
    
    Note: Children: iterable, [key], value, body
    Let iterable be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_iterable be proc translate_expression with ctx, iterable
    
    Note: Store foreach metadata for later reconstruction
    Let hir_foreach be proc hir_create_foreach from HIR with hir_iterable
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_foreach, "source_language", "php"
    
    Return hir_foreach
End Process

@Reasoning:
`switch (subject) { case_clauses default }`. PHP switch uses loose
comparison (==) which matters for the executor; the HIR preserves that
distinction.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate subject expression; iterate case clauses translating each;
build HIR switch node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_switch_statement" takes ctx as Integer, switch_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with switch_node
    
    Let expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr
    
    Let hir_switch be proc hir_create_switch from HIR with hir_expr
    
    Note: Translate cases
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 1
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let case_clause be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_case be proc translate_case_clause with ctx, case_clause
        proc hir_switch_add_case from HIR with hir_switch, hir_case
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_switch
End Process

@Reasoning:
A single case/default clause inside switch. PHP cases fall through
implicitly unless break/return ends them - the HIR preserves the
original statement list so the executor handles fall-through.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read value expression (or is_default flag); translate each statement
in the clause body; build HIR case node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_case_clause" takes ctx as Integer, case_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with case_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    
    Let first be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, first
    
    Let hir_case be proc hir_create_case from HIR with hir_value
    
    Note: Translate case body
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc hir_case_add_statement from HIR with hir_case, hir_stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_case
End Process

@Reasoning:
`return [expr];`. Bare return is allowed in PHP (returns null).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read optional value; if present translate; build HIR return node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_return_statement" takes ctx as Integer, return_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with return_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return proc hir_create_return from HIR with 0
    End If
    
    Let expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr
    
    Return proc hir_create_return from HIR with hir_expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
`try block catch (Type1|Type2 $e) { handler } ... finally { cleanup }`.
Multi-type catch (PHP 8.0+) is supported via the union-type syntax. The
finally block is optional.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate try body; iterate catch clauses translating each (catch type
union plus handler body); translate finally if present.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_try_statement" takes ctx as Integer, try_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with try_node
    
    Let try_body be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_try_body be proc translate_statement with ctx, try_body
    
    Let hir_try be proc hir_create_try from HIR with hir_try_body
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_try, "source_language", "php"
    
    Note: Store catch/finally clauses in metadata
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let clause be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let clause_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with clause
        
        If clause_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_CATCH_CLAUSE:
            Let hir_catch be proc translate_statement with ctx, clause
            proc hir_try_add_catch from HIR with hir_try, hir_catch
        End If
        
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_try
End Process

@Reasoning:
`throw expr;`. PHP 8 made throw an expression too, but we translate it
as a statement here; expression-form throws come through
translate_expression.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate the exception expression; build HIR throw node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_throw_statement" takes ctx as Integer, throw_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with throw_node
    Let expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr
    
    Return proc hir_create_throw from HIR with hir_expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
`echo expr, expr, expr;` outputs all expressions concatenated. Lowered
to a call to a built-in echo helper in HIR with each expression as a
separate argument.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Iterate echo arguments translating each; build HIR call to "echo"
builtin with the argument list.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_echo_statement" takes ctx as Integer, echo_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate echo as print function call
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with echo_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    
    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call from HIR with "print"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "source_language", "php"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "php_echo", "true"
    
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with ctx, expr
        proc hir_call_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_expr
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_call
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The central expression dispatcher: literals, variables, binary/unary/
ternary ops, assignment, function/method calls, new, member access,
indexing, array literals. Each routes through a dedicated helper.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read expr_node type; switch through all PHP_EXPR_* tags dispatching
to translate_<kind>_expr. Default: error/skip.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with expr_node
    
    Note: Literals
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_NUMBER_LITERAL:
        Let value be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_literal from HIR with "number", value
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_STRING_LITERAL:
        Set value to proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_literal from HIR with "string", value
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_BOOLEAN_LITERAL:
        Set value to proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_literal from HIR with "boolean", value
    End If
    
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_NULL_LITERAL:
        Return proc hir_create_literal from HIR with "null", "null"
    End If
    
    Note: Variable
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_VARIABLE:
        Set value to proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_variable from HIR with value
    End If
    
    Note: Identifier
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_IDENTIFIER:
        Set value to proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with value
    End If
    
    Note: Binary expression
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_binary_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Unary expression
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_unary_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Ternary expression
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_TERNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_ternary_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Assignment
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_ASSIGN_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_assign_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Function call
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_CALL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_call_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: New expression
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_NEW_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_new_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Member access
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_MEMBER_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_member_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Array access
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_index_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Note: Array literal
    If node_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_ARRAY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_array_expr with ctx, expr_node
    End If
    
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
`left OP right`. PHP operator semantics differ from C in subtle ways
(== is loose equality, === is strict). The operator string is passed
through verbatim so the executor applies the correct rules.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate left and right; read operator; build HIR binary expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_binary_expr" takes ctx as Integer, binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with binary_node
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with binary_node
    Let left be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let right be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_left be proc translate_expression with ctx, left
    Let hir_right be proc translate_expression with ctx, right
    
    Return proc hir_create_binary_op from HIR with operator, hir_left, hir_right
End Process

@Reasoning:
Unary operators: !, -, ~, ++, --. Prefix vs postfix tracked separately
for ++/--.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate operand; read operator and prefix flag; build HIR unary
expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_unary_expr" takes ctx as Integer, unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with unary_node
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with unary_node
    Let operand be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand
    
    Return proc hir_create_unary_op from HIR with operator, hir_operand
End Process

@Reasoning:
`cond ? then : else`. PHP also supports the short form `cond ?: else`
(returns cond if truthy else 'else') which arrives with the then
branch null.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate cond, then (or null for short form), else; build HIR
conditional expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_ternary_expr" takes ctx as Integer, ternary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with ternary_node
    
    Let condition be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let then_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    Let else_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 2
    
    Let hir_condition be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
    Let hir_then be proc translate_expression with ctx, then_expr
    Let hir_else be proc translate_expression with ctx, else_expr
    
    Return proc hir_create_ternary from HIR with hir_condition, hir_then, hir_else
End Process

@Reasoning:
`lhs = rhs` or compound forms `+=`, `.=`, etc. Distinct from a binary
expression because assignment is its own HIR construct (lvalue
requirements differ).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate target and value; read operator; build HIR assignment node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_assign_expr" takes ctx as Integer, assign_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with assign_node
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with assign_node
    Let target be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_target be proc translate_expression with ctx, target
    Let hir_value be proc translate_expression with ctx, value
    
    Return proc hir_create_assign from HIR with operator, hir_target, hir_value
End Process

@Reasoning:
`callee(args...)`. Supports both function calls and method calls
(callee may be a member-access expression). Named arguments (PHP 8.0+)
are emitted as named args in the HIR.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate callee; iterate args translating each (positional or named);
build HIR call expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_call_expr" takes ctx as Integer, call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with call_node
    
    Let callee be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_callee be proc translate_expression with ctx, callee
    
    Note: Extract function name for HIR
    Let callee_type be proc php_ast_node_type from PHPParser with callee
    Let function_name be ""
    
    If callee_type is equal to PHPParser.PHP_IDENTIFIER:
        Set function_name to proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with callee
    Otherwise:
        Set function_name to "anonymous"
    End If
    
    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call from HIR with function_name
    
    Note: Translate arguments
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg
        proc hir_call_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_arg
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
`new ClassName(args)`. Constructor invocation. The class name may be a
qualified name; the HIR carries it as a fully-qualified reference.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Read class name; iterate constructor args; build HIR new expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_new_expr" takes ctx as Integer, new_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let class_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with new_node
    
    Let hir_new be proc hir_create_new from HIR with class_name
    
    Note: Translate constructor arguments
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with new_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg
        proc hir_new_add_argument from HIR with hir_new, hir_arg
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_new
End Process

@Reasoning:
`obj->member` (instance access) or `Class::member` (static access).
The HIR distinguishes via a flag because static access is
semantically different.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate base; read member name and is_static flag; build HIR member
access node.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_member_expr" takes ctx as Integer, member_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let member_name be proc php_ast_node_value from PHPParser with member_node
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with member_node
    Let object be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with ctx, object
    
    Return proc hir_create_member_access from HIR with hir_object, member_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
`array[index]` or `array{index}` (deprecated form). PHP arrays are
associative, so the index may be any expression yielding a value usable
as a key.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Translate base and index; build HIR index expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_index_expr" takes ctx as Integer, index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with index_node
    
    Let array be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let index be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
    
    Let hir_array be proc translate_expression with ctx, array
    Let hir_index be proc translate_expression with ctx, index
    
    Return proc hir_create_index_access from HIR with hir_array, hir_index
End Process

@Reasoning:
`[key => value, value, ...]` or `array(...)`. PHP arrays mix sequential
and associative entries; the HIR builds an array literal preserving
both kinds of entries with their explicit-or-implicit keys.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Iterate elements; for each, translate optional key (or null for
sequential) and required value; build HIR array literal.
@End Implementation
Process called "translate_array_expr" takes ctx as Integer, array_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_array be proc hir_create_array from HIR
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_array, "source_language", "php"
    
    Let children be proc php_ast_node_children from PHPParser with array_node
    Let count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
    Let i be 0
    
    While i is less than count:
        Let element be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
        Let hir_element be proc translate_expression with ctx, element
        proc hir_array_add_element from HIR with hir_array, hir_element
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    
    Return hir_array
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC API
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point alias for translate_php_to_hir. Kept for backward
compatibility with callers using the shorter name.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Delegates to translate_php_to_hir.
@End Implementation
Process called "php_to_hir" takes php_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc translate_php_to_hir from php_ast
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public single-arg facade invoked by the translation dispatcher's
LANG_PHP arm. Wires the full source -> HIR pipeline: PHPParser
parse_php_source lexes + parses to a PHP_PROGRAM AST root, then
translate_php_to_hir walks the AST into HIR. On parse failure (0
return from parse_php_source) the wrapper short-circuits to 0 so
the caller observes a parse-only failure without a translator NPE.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
ast = PHPParser.parse_php_source(source); if ast == 0 return 0;
return translate_php_to_hir(ast). The intermediate AST is consumed
by translate_php_to_hir and the caller does not need to free it
explicitly (lifetime is tied to the global arena used by the
PHP frontend).
@End Implementation

Process called "php_to_hir_from_source" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let php_ast be proc parse_php_source from PHPParser with source_code
    If php_ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc translate_php_to_hir with php_ast
End Process
